[[File:Bartender (Dragon Inn) chathead.png|left]]
The '''Bartender''' of the [[Dragon Inn]] plays a small role in the [[quest]] [[Zogre Flesh Eaters]], where the players must show him the [[Dragon inn tankard]] in order to learn that it once belonged to the late [[Brentle Vahn]]. He also features in [[Alfred Grimhand's Barcrawl]], where he sells the player a Fire Brandy for {{NoCoins|12}} coins.

Additionally, it appears that the bartender is knowledgeable about the gossip of [[Yanille]] and its community, as he seems well acquainted with the gossip thereof. As such, during the quest he is able to reveal the whereabouts of Brentle prior to his "disappearance", and signs a portrait of [[Sithik Ints]] to verify his identity.

As with all bartenders, he of course sells various alcoholic beverages. [[Dragon bitter]], [[Greenman's ale]] and [[Beer]] are all available for purchase, however the player has to navigate through some dialogue trees.

According to Mod West, [[Madame Caldarium]] is his wife, and {{RSL|Balnea}}, who players meet during the quest As a First Resort in ''RuneScape'', is her daughter. {{CiteTwitter|author=Mod West|url=https://twitter.com/JagexAsh/status/920581364457582592|date=8 December 2017|archiveurl=https://archive.is/LyNmY|archivedate=27 May 2020|quote=[Is Madame Caldarium actually Balnea from the live game?] Nope, she is her mother and the Dragon Inn barkeep is her husband. Not sure there is a reference to that in game, but that's the canon.}}

